review_blob: Wonderful citrus hop aroma.  Clear golden ipa that tastes as good as it smells. Nice rounded palate thats clean and fresh. A real winner.

Didn?t care for this beer. Looked clear and crisp, but it had a funky aftertaste. The more I drank the less noticeable the aftertaste. I would not recommend this  unless it was the only beer in the fridge on a hot summer day.

Citrus aroma with a gold copper appearance. A nice crisp but not bitter grapefruit taste, from theincredible cascade dry hopping. Taste great through to finish. I was pleasantly surprised at how good this kosher brew tastes.

Due South Brewery just opened yesterday.  May 12, 2013. Initial flavor was good,  good combination of malt and hops. After a few seconds my palate was hit with some very sweet notes. I didnt care for the sweet flavor combined with the bitterness of a hopped ale. Perhaps I just need to get used to the abundance of flavors.
Due South Brewery just opened yesterday May 12, 2012. Nice malty chocolate smell and taste. Had a typical oatmeal stout flavor, with some heavy hopiness. Nice blend of hops and chocolate overtones.
